Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Friday and welcome back to our 82nd Weekly Dose of Optimism. The boys=
 (and gals) were buzzin=E2=80=99 this week. You can feel the energy in the =
air. That energy was so magnetic that Packy actually booked a flight out to=
 the Gundo to meet with founders and builders this week. I=E2=80=99m sure h=
e=E2=80=99ll have much to share.=20
But until then, let=E2=80=99s get to it.
Today=E2=80=99s Not Boring is brought to you by=E2=80=A6Percent [ https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/5607100d-9e13-4f4c-ac12-5dfa1b7d57e0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
High yield, income generation, diversification and greater resistance to in=
flation and volatility =E2=80=94 are just some of the factors that have att=
racted investors to private credit in recent years.=C2=A0
