100d-9e13-4f4c-ac12-5dfa1b7d57e0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZj=
mlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] + a $500 welcome bonus when you sign up today.
(1) Gemma: Introducing new state-of-the-art open models [ https://substack.=
com/redirect/64c4254d-8a35-4cae-85c4-499d29fb9463?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb=
8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
From Google
Gemma [ https://substack.com/redirect/d46869aa-175d-461b-b956-431e6bec38a0?=
j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is a f=
amily of lightweight, state-of-the-art open models [ https://substack.com/r=
edirect/a902b16f-3e6e-4557-a71f-c5f55dbf2926?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7=
GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] built from the same research and tec=
hnology used to create the Gemini [ https://substack.com/redirect/332c0106-=
8583-4749-bca2-648401fcbbad?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] models. Developed by Google DeepMind and other teams =
across Google, Gemma is inspired by Gemini, and the name reflects the Latin=
 gemma, meaning =E2=80=9Cprecious stone.=E2=80=9D
Weird week for Google!=20
Last week, it announced its upgraded Gemini 1.5 with longer context windows=
 =E2=80=94 1 million in Gemini 1.5 Pro =E2=80=94 and people have used it to=
 do some really mindblowing things, like feed it hours of video and ask ver=
y specific questions that it seems to get consistently right, or show it sc=
reen recordings and ask it to write code to automate whatever you recorded =
(like look for an apartment on Zillow [ https://substack.com/redirect/63a85=
1c4-45e8-4a04-9e43-5a4749809869?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjm=
lXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]). Great!=20
On the other hand=E2=80=A6 its image generator absolutely refused to make i=
mages of white people [ https://substack.com/redirect/1e0b2a46-4566-4f47-86=
e5-8b06020938e6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU ]. Not great!=20
In the plus column, Google is joining Meta=E2=80=99s rank in open sourcing =
versions of its powerful Gemini model. This is a big deal, not only because=
 the technology is now open sourced and available to developers, but also b=
ecause another major tech company is signaling its views on AI safety. And =
that view is essentially: open artificial intelligence is safer than closed=
 artificial intelligence. Ironically, OpenAI is now the least open of the b=
ig three here (OpenAI, Meta, Google.) There are certainly tradeoffs and com=
panies need to make individual decisions that benefit its stakeholders =E2=
=80=94 and to be clear, Google and Meta are not altruistically open sourcin=
g their AI models =E2=80=94 but our view is that freely shared AI is better=
 for the world than closed AI. It increases the pace of innovation and allo=
ws developers to identify and patch up potentially dangerous aspects of the=
 technology.
Now of course, both Google and Meta will continue to keep the most advanced=
 technologies under close wraps (and charge customers for it), but tomorrow=
=E2=80=99s open source model will be more powerful than today=E2=80=99s clo=
sed model.
(2) MEGA-CRISPR tool gives a power boost to cancer-fighting cells [ https:/=
/substack.com/redirect/0adee4c2-018c-4d56-82b3-209747ff074c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXA=
wZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Sara Reardon for Nature
Now, a CRISPR-based system that targets a cell=E2=80=99s short-lived messen=
ger RNA instead of DNA could provide a more precise and reversible way of d=
esigning cell therapies [ https://substack.com/redirect/9dceb2fa-174b-4a98-=
bc07-05103476dc61?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU ] =E2=80=94 and even help scientists to discover how different ge=
nes work together.
Another week, another big story in gene editing.=20
A new CRISPR methodology called MEGA uses Cas13d edits RNA instead of DNA, =
which reduces the risk of permanent genetic changes. Editing RNA means MEGA=
 can make temporary adjustments to cell behavior, instead of long-term gene=
tic mutations. MEGA=E2=80=99s approach is particularly beneficial for rejuv=
enating exhausted CAR T cells in cancer therapy, enhancing their effectiven=
ess against tumors. We=E2=80=99re still only working with models and mice h=
ere, but MEGA=E2=80=99s combination of reversibility and controllability co=
uld lead to safer and more efficient gene therapies in the not-so-distant f=
uture.
(3) SPACE!
A massive week in space. There are four big stories that are caught our att=
ention:
Varda Comes Home [ https://substack.com/redirect/a2e96b4e-b45f-4692-b424-e9=
1dd1dd370b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU ]: On Wednesday, Varda=E2=80=99s W-1 Mission re-entry capsule touched do=
wn in Utah.
Moon Landing [ https://substack.com/redirect/d9067ec7-954b-40e2-a7fa-bf0b00=
0d6bd8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]=
: Intuitive Machine=E2=80=99s spacecraft made a lunar landing yesterday, be=
coming the first privately built spacecraft to do so. It was also the first=
 American vehicle to land on the moon in more than 50 years.
Glenn=E2=80=99s New Erection [ https://substack.com/redirect/d7644c97-5dcd-=
4098-95cc-0c139331187f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]: Blue Origin=E2=80=99s New Glenn vehicle successfully roll=
ed out and upended today for the first time on the pad at Launch Complex 36=
 (LC-36).
Disney Space CEO [ https://substack.com/redirect/7f7f9987-6983-4d2a-ab7f-0e=
97c85ebd43?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU ]: Former Disney star is now the CEO of a Founders Fund/a16z backed spac=
e data company [ https://substack.com/redirect/8c8a8a37-51d9-4ff9-9f7c-8844=
46272e7a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ]. How often do we get to share articles from E! News? This was the cross-=
over we didn=E2=80=99t know we needed.
(4) Hadrian Series B [ http://Hadrian Automation=E2=80=99s CEO wants to def=
y history and revitalize American industry ]
As a result of this effort, which was completed last December, the company =
closed a $117 million Series B. With the new funding, Power is aiming to do=
uble the automation and software team in order to improve the automation pr=
ocesses and meet new customer demand.
With all of this space action, we=E2=80=99re going to need more rocket manu=
facturing capacity and automation. Thankfully, Hadrian just secured an addi=
tional $117M in Series B funding to scale out its footprint and to meet boo=
ming customer demand. As a reminder, Hadrian automates high-precision CNC m=
achining processes in aerospace and defense manufacturing, aiming to signif=
icantly improve efficiency and scalability through software and robotics.
Almost two years ago, Not Boring covered what Hadrian was up to in Hadrian:=
 Ex Machina Ad Lunam [ https://substack.com/redirect/0e1fc243-91a6-44ba-98c=
f-81fa6d72c8db?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU ]. At the time, the company had recently closed its $90M Series A an=
d in the subsequent months has established itself as one of the leading tec=
hno-industrial startups in the country. Now, it=E2=80=99s looking to grow i=
ts software and automation teams and expand its factory footprint.=20
If you have 30 minutes this weekend, watch John Coogan=E2=80=99s documentar=
y on Hadrian and get inspired to build things.=20
(5) A Techno-Industrialist Manifesto [ https://substack.com/redirect/bc4f27=
a9-8e48-445c-a399-e97bdd9374be?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjml=
XXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Aaron Slodov for Pirate Wires
The most valuable thing to pursue is also the hardest; rebuilding a moderni=
zed US industrial base will take trillions of dollars, but will also extend=
 our prosperity and abundance into the next millennium.
American Dynamism. Hard Startups. Bits and Atoms. Techno-Industrials. Gundo=
=2E
Whatever you want to call it, it=E2=80=99s a movement.=20
Technologists and startup founders are increasingly working on hard/hardwar=
e projects that could =E2=80=94 if successful=E2=80=94 have a meaningful im=
pact on the physical world that we live in. Aaron Slodov [ https://substack=
=2Ecom/redirect/c4bd4aa3-14b3-482f-a92=
f-86d4acbec79f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.g=
b8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], founder of Atomic Industries,=
 tries to capture this movement in his recent essay for Pirate Wires.
Slodov advocates for revitalizing the U.S. manufacturing sector through tec=
hnological innovation, arguing that manufacturing is crucial for sustained =
economic growth and national security. This revitalization will require the=
 integration of best-in-class software into a new, modernized industrial ba=
se. And it will require our country=E2=80=99s best and brightest shifting t=
heir focus from churning out software towards building out our country=E2=
=80=99s industrial base.
The last 40 years of technological progress has left many of our nation=E2=
=80=99s best and brightest incomprehensibly rich. Just think how many softw=
are founders have made over $100M in the last decade alone. That=E2=80=99s =
awesome and good for them. But now it=E2=80=99s time for those folks to re-=
invest their talents and learnings into building back our country.
If you have some time this weekend, check out Percent [ https://substack.co=
m/redirect/5607100d-9e13-4f4c-ac12-5dfa1b7d57e0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J=
5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
We=E2=80=99ll be back in your inbox on Tuesday.
Thanks for reading,
Dan + Packy

